      Modifier and Type Method Description
      private void addCut​(Problem problem, java.lang.Double[] cut)
      This functions adds the given cut to the given Problem.

      Cut format:
      {1d, 0d, 0d, 7.5d, 50d}
      Last value represents the b column.
      The rest represent coefficient multiplicators.
      The restriction is a <= restriction.

      The given example would look like this:
      1*x1 + 0*x2 + 0*x3 + 7,5*x4 <= 50

      FPP.LinearOptimization.Data.IBendersOptimizationSolutionData solve​(FPP.LinearOptimization.Data.BendersOptimizationData bendersOptimizationData)  
      private java.lang.Double[] solveProblem​(java.lang.Double[][] simplexTableau, boolean solveAbleWithBAndB, boolean max)
      Solves a SimplexTableau with Simplex or BranchAndBound.

      Solution format:
      {10d, 0d, 130d, 2d}
      Last value represents the solution type.
      Second to last represents optimal function value.
      The rest represent variable values.
      For more information see return of Simplex.loese().
      private void stepZeroCut​(MasterProblem masterProblem, SubProblem subProblem, Problem dualProblem, java.lang.Double[] yZeroes)
      This method calculates the first cut in step 0, with all u-values set to 0 and adds the cut to the MasterProblem.

      To set all u-values to 0 all function values are set to 0.
      The SimplexTableau is then solved as usual.
      private java.lang.Double substituteConstant​(FPP.LinearOptimization.Data.BendersOptimizationData bendersOptimizationData)
      This method substitutes the constant of the simplex tableau function with 0 and returns that constant.
      This is done because Simplex & BAndB can not handle that in the right way.

      If there is no constant in the function, Double.NaN is returned.
      ATTENTION: constant value has to be added to the optimal solution to get the right result!
      private void updateSubproblem​(SubProblem subProblem, Problem dualProblem, java.lang.Double[] y)
      Inserts y-values into function of the DualProblem so that the u-values can be calculated later.

      • substituteConstant

        private java.lang.Double substituteConstant​(FPP.LinearOptimization.Data.BendersOptimizationData bendersOptimizationData)
        This method substitutes the constant of the simplex tableau function with 0 and returns that constant.
        This is done because Simplex & BAndB can not handle that in the right way.

        If there is no constant in the function, Double.NaN is returned.
        ATTENTION: constant value has to be added to the optimal solution to get the right result!
        Parameters:
        bendersOptimizationData -
        Returns:
        constant of given function

      • stepZeroCut

        private void stepZeroCut​(MasterProblem masterProblem,
                         SubProblem subProblem,
                         Problem dualProblem,
                         java.lang.Double[] yZeroes)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method calculates the first cut in step 0, with all u-values set to 0 and adds the cut to the MasterProblem.

        To set all u-values to 0 all function values are set to 0.
        The SimplexTableau is then solved as usual.
        Parameters:
        masterProblem - MasterProblem
        subProblem - SubProblem
        dualProblem - DualProblem as Problem
        yZeroes - array with 0-values
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if not solvable

      • buildOptimalSolution

        private java.lang.Double[] buildOptimalSolution​(FPP.LinearOptimization.Data.BendersOptimizationData bendersOptimizationData,
                                                java.lang.Double[] solution,
                                                java.lang.Double[] optimalY,
                                                java.lang.Double[] functionMasterY,
                                                java.lang.Double[] functionSubX,
                                                java.lang.Double constant)
        Builds the optimal solution found by the BendersAlgorithm.

        Optimal solution format:
        {4d, 4d, 0d, 0.5d, 1d, 1430d}
        The last value represents optimal function value.
        The rest represent optimal x and y values on their respective positions.
        Parameters:
        bendersOptimizationData - BendersOptimizationData object
        solution - array of optimal SubProblem solution values (with inserted optimal y-values)
        optimalY - array of final optimal y-values
        functionMasterY - function of MasterProblem
        functionSubX - function of SubProblem
        constant - the constant of the initial input-function, 0 if there was none
        Returns:
        array of the optimal solutions

      • solveProblem

        private java.lang.Double[] solveProblem​(java.lang.Double[][] simplexTableau,
                                        boolean solveAbleWithBAndB,
                                        boolean max)
        Solves a SimplexTableau with Simplex or BranchAndBound.

        Solution format:
        {10d, 0d, 130d, 2d}
        Last value represents the solution type.
        Second to last represents optimal function value.
        The rest represent variable values.
        For more information see return of Simplex.loese().
        Parameters:
        simplexTableau -
        solveAbleWithBAndB - boolean if solvable with BAndB
        max - true if maximize, false if minimize
        Returns:
        solution as Double[]

        Returns:

        private boolean restrictionContainsOnlyY​(java.lang.Double[] restriction,
                                         int[] yIndices)
        Returns true if a restrictions contains only y-values.

        Restriction format:
        {1d, 0d, 0d, 7.5d, 50d}
        Last value represents the b column.
        The rest represent coefficient multiplicators.
        The restriction is a <= restriction.

        With y at position 1 the given example would look like this:
        1*y1 + 0*x2 + 0*x3 + 7,5*x4 <= 50
        Parameters:
        restriction - array representing a restriction
        yIndices - array with y-positions of the given restriction
